Student Management System
=========================

CLASS DESCRIPTION
-----------------
Student.java
-Represents student info with (ID, name, email, gpa, major, and year)
-Includes and overrides toString,equals, and hashCode
-Implements Comparable<Student> for generic methods

StudentManager.java
-Manages students using ArrayList<Student>
-Has methods like add, remove, find students, gpa calculation
-Contains filter methods for major, year, and honor roll
-Returns total num of students and list of different majors

Course.java
-Contains course info (courseCode, courseName, credits, instructor, and maxEnrollment)
-Uses ArrayList<String> to store prerequisites
-Implements methods like addPrerequisites, hasPrerequisites, and getPrerequisites

CourseManager.java
-Manages different courses through ArrayList<Course>
-Has add, find, get course by instructor, getAvailableCourses, and printAllCourses

Enrollment.java
-Stores enrollment information like (enrollment Id, student id, course code, grade, and semester)
-has method getGradePoints for grade conversion from letter to decimal
-has method isPassing as edge to make sure the only letter grade you get is either 'A', 'B', 'C', 'D', and not 'F'

EnrollmentManager.java
-Enrolls students via enrollment info and manages them via ArrayList<Enrollment>
-Prevents duplicates, has methods drop enrollment, find enrollment, get enrollment, and assign grade
-Also calculates student GPA from all enrolled courses, can print enrollment info

ArrayListOperationsDemo.java
-Demos turning array into arraylist, arraylist to array
-Shows subList behavior, sorting with comparator, and searching via indexOf, contains, and binarySearch

ArrayListVsArrayDemo.java
-Demos arrays vs arraylist comparison, measures time and performance of adding students and accessing students

ArrayListUtils.java
-Generic utilities implementation with swap, findMax, filter, reverse, merge
-Showcase bounded generics like sum, average, and filterAbove
-Introduces wildcards upper bound, lower bound, and unbounded

GenericList.java
-Wrapper classes used on ArrayList<T>
-has getAll, addAll, and addAllFrom to add from arraylist and other generic lists

-GenericStack.java
-Stack implementation with ArrayList<T>
-methods push, pop, peek, size, isEmpty, clear

GenericQueue.java
-Queue implementation with ArrayList<T>
-methods enqueue, dequeue, peek, size, isEmpty

Pokemon Generics Lab.Pair.java
-Pokemon Generics Lab.Pair class with generics
-fields first and second pair, getters and setters, toString, equals, and hashCode

StudentManagementSystemMain.java
-Houses the interactive menu that implements all the main managers like StudentManager, CourseManager, and EnrollmentManager
-Contains menu option for adding student, removing student, finding student, adding course, enrolling student to course,
assigning course grade, calculate gpa(all courses), and generates report

ReportGenerator.java
-Uses the manager classes to generate report of student info, course info, major info, and honor roll info

HOW TO COMPILE & RUN
--------------------
-Compile files
-Run StudentManagementSystemMain.java
-Run ArrayListOperationsDemo.java
-Run ArrayListVsArrayDemo.java

DESIGN DECISIONS
----------------
-No null edge case for Enrollment grade
-Enrollment ID are automatically generated
-Using ArrayList for students, courses, and enrollments for size change
-Prerequisites are stored as strings

CHALLENGES ENCOUNTERED
----------------------
-Handling as much edge cases as I can think of and testing
-Careful use of type bounds for Generic methods to distinguish from raw types
-Syntax difficulty
-Understanding comparator approach

WHAT I LEARNED ABOUT ARRAYLISTS AND GENERICS
--------------------------------------------
-Use arraylist for size changes and anything that has to do with adding removing and resizing
-Generic methods can be recycled for different types
-Bounded generics ensure method safety

COMPARISON OF ARRAYLIST VS ARRAY
--------------------------------
Arrays
-More tedious, adding and removing requires manual shifting and resizing
-Allows direct access to data

ArrayList
-Adding, removing, and resizing is easier. Array will automatically grow and shrink.
-O(1) time complexity
-Easier to use and manage

